# Development configuration
VITE_QA_MODE=true

# Parity path configuration (optional - defaults to current working directory)
PARITY_ROOT_DIR=.
PARITY_DIR=./parity
PARITY_FIXTURES_DIR=./parity/fixtures

# Server configuration
PORT=4000
NODE_ENV=development

# Production deployment notes:
# - Set NODE_ENV=production to hide error stack traces
# - Use absolute paths for PARITY_DIR in containers: /app/parity
# - Ensure PARITY_FIXTURES_DIR points to: /app/parity/fixtures
# - Server will auto-create /parity/out/ directory for reports
# 
# Example production values:
# NODE_ENV=production
# PARITY_DIR=/app/parity
# PARITY_FIXTURES_DIR=/app/parity/fixtures
# PORT=4000

# Operations:
# - Add new scenarios by creating folders in PARITY_FIXTURES_DIR
# - Each scenario needs: engine_inputs.json + CSV files for each statement
# - Run checks via API: POST /api/parity/run {"scenario":"name"}
# - Fetch saved reports: GET /api/parity/report/:scenario
# - Reports cached with ETag headers for efficient retrieval